  "text": "Other Swansea criteria parameters Serum creatinine (Cr), urate and urea fall by approximately 25% early in first trimester due to a 50%-60% rise in renal plasma flow and glomerular filtration rate. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Towards the end of third trimester, renal plasma flow declines to preconception rates and Cr trends back towards pre-conception values.",
